e) that non-GSO FSS systems that operate in the frequency band 12.75-13.25 GHz (Earth- to-space) may also operate in the frequency band 10.7-10.95 GHz (space-to-Earth) in accordance with No. 5.441;
f) that the potential interference impact from unwanted emissions produced by non-GSO FSS systems communicating with A-ESIMs and M-ESIMs in the frequency band 10.7-10.95 GHz (space-to-Earth) in accordance with No. 5.441, into passive sensors of the EESS operating in the adjacent frequency band 10.6-10.7 GHz, should be studied to ensure protection of existing and future use of the frequency band by the EESS (passive); – 190 –
RES133-3
g) that the current use and future development of existing services in the frequency band should be protected from unacceptable interference caused by operation of A-ESIMs and M-ESIMs communicating with non-GSO space stations in the frequency band;
h) that interference management mechanisms, including necessary mitigation measures, are required for the operation of non-GSO ESIMs to protect other space and terrestrial services to which the frequency band referred to in considering a) are allocated,
