c) that, under Nos. 15.12 and 15.13, administrations shall take all practicable and necessary steps to ensure that the operation of electrical apparatus or installations, including those for WPT, does not cause harmful interference to a radiocommunication service and, in particular, to a radionavigation or any other safety service;
d) that some administrations regard WPT as an industrial, scientific and medical (ISM) application defined by the Radio Regulations, and that they apply their current regulations to the ISM applications and equipment;
